Names and GEOIDs of regional MSAs

Source: R/data.R
msa.Rd

A reference dataset of all the metropolitan statistical areas (MSAs) in the US, marked with whether they're in a New England state.

Usage

msa

Format

A data frame with 392 rows and 3 variables:

geoid

GEOID/FIPS code

name

Name of MSA

region

String: whether MSA is inside or outside of New England

Source

US Census Bureau via tidycensus. Note that these are as of 2020.

See also

Other ref-datasets: acs_vars, ct5_clusters, decennial_vars, naics_codes, neighborhood_tracts, occ_codes, proxy_pumas, regions, school_dists, table_nums, village2town, xwalk, zip2town
